Italy, however, with the exception of the district about Rome, was subject to certain payments in kind (annona), whence its division into Italia annonaria and Italia urbicaria. According to some, Italia urbicaria contributed to the use of the metropolis payments similar to those which Italia annonaria paid to the· imperial household. Moreover, to compensate for her im- munity from other taxation, Italy paid 5 per cent. on all testa- mentary successions (vicesima hereditatum) and 5 per cent. on the value of all manumitted slaves, Livy, 7, 16.
